  - "Noether-like theorem"
  - "graph dynamics"
  - "Lyapunov stability"
  - "reproducible experiment"
abstract: >-
  We present a structural continuity result for grammar-constrained dynamics
  on finite graphs within the TNFR (Resonant Fractal Nature Theory) formalism.
  Admissible operator sequences, restricted by unified grammar rules U1-U6,
  induce a charge-like structural quantity and an associated current satisfying
  an approximate discrete continuity equation. We formulate the continuity
  statement, derive a Lyapunov-type energy corollary, and provide a compact
  computational benchmark across five graph topologies with fixed seeds.
  Experiments show bounded conservation under valid sequences and measurable
  degradation when grammatical constraints are violated.
